        question: "What is the clinical significance of Janeway lesions versus Osler nodes in IE?",
        options: ["They are identical findings", "Janeway lesions are PAINLESS (septic emboli in dermis); Osler nodes are PAINFUL (immune complex deposition) — both indicate active IE with embolization", "Janeway lesions are only found in subacute IE", "Neither is clinically significant"],
        correct: 1,
        rationale: "Janeway lesions (painless erythematous macules on palms/soles) result from septic microemboli. Osler nodes (painful nodules on fingertips/toes) result from immune complex deposition. Both are peripheral manifestations of active IE and indicate ongoing embolization."
