        correct: 1,
        rationale: "The cardiothoracic ratio compares heart width to thoracic width on a PA film. >0.5 (heart wider than half the thorax) indicates cardiomegaly. This is only reliable on PA films — AP/portable films magnify the heart and may falsely suggest cardiomegaly."
